Brian, Theresa,

Over the past month we have added the ability to deploy
IndigoMetrics/Inclign via a virtual machine on AWS - even for small scale
deployments.

Up until now our approach has been to only use a dedicated machine for
larger scale deployment, but now we can now spin up a VM that only holds one
customer's data even for small scale deployments. This gives the customer
the knowledge that the data is protected by AWS's architecture, allows them
to specify any particular data control protocols they would like and also
allows us to give the customer access to the VM so that they can monitor
data flows. The Indigo/Inclign code is housed in a protected area of the VM
so that the customer cannot access our IP.

Its still easier for us to house pilots on our non-cloud infrastructure and
there is a cost to a new VM so we prefer not to use it for free pilots - but
if you have a customer that is data control focussed this gives us the
ability to put them on a dedicated architecture from day one and scale their
scheme up easily. 

Chris 

 


